</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SB1080:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SB1080"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SB &#xA;              1080-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Bill
              
                        No. 1080</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 12</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to amend Section 26807 of, and to add Section 26807.5 to, the Government Code, relating to local government. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Approved  by
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Governor
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 17, 2026.
                      </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 17, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SB 1080, Valladares.
                          County clerks: certification of records: signature.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law requires the county clerk to act as the clerk of the board of supervisors in the county and to perform specified duties, including, among other things, to take charge of, safely keep, or dispose of pursuant to law all books, papers, and records that are filed or deposited in their office pursuant to law. Existing law requires the county clerk to keep an official seal of their office for use when performing official duties.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would authorize the county clerk to use a printed, stamped, photographically reproduced facsimile, electronic, or otherwise digitally created signature in certifying to a record in the county clerk’s office, provided that the certification includes the official seal of the county clerk’s office affixed thereto. The bill would make nonsubstantive changes, including eliminating gendered pronouns.
		</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.856104705558238"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 26807 of the Government Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_A936F20B-76DC-48DE-9368-4E8E9D17B42D"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">26807.</h6> (a) The county clerk shall keep an official seal of their office for use when performing official duties other than ex officio duties which shall, when embossed, stamped, impressed or affixed to a certification, show legibly. The
				  seal shall: (a) be circular in shape; (b) be not less than 1<font size="2"><sup>1</sup>/<sub>4</sub></font> inches in diameter; (c) have in the center any words or design adopted by the county clerk; (d) have inscribed around the central words or design, “County Clerk, ____ County, California”, inserting therein the name of the county.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) Nothing contained herein shall prohibit a county clerk from continuing to use a seal of a design different than that specified herein if
				  the seal has customarily been used prior to the effective date of
				  Section 1 of Chapter 564 of the Statutes of 1968.</div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s20.08853524217799724"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 2.</h3> Section 26807.5 is added to the Government Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_C6541DC4-EC9A-4043-A783-B1D60B21BAC4"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">26807.5.</h6> The county clerk may use a printed, stamped, photographically reproduced facsimile, electronic, or otherwise digitally created signature in certifying to a record in the county clerk’s office, provided that the certification includes the official seal of the county clerk’s office affixed thereto.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
